definition.value: A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
An aliphatic alcohol in which the aliphatic alkane chain is substituted by a hydroxy group at unspecified position.
The  acetate ester of 2-methylbutan-1-ol.
A 3beta-sterol that consists of 4beta-methylzymosterol in which the 4alpha-hydrogen is replaced by a carboxy group.
A 3-oxo-5alpha- steroid that is zymosterol which has been substituted by a methyl group at C-4, and in which the 3-hydroxy function has been oxidised to an oxo group.
A molecule consisting of a graphene cylinder or two or more concentric graphene cylinders.

A carbon nanotube consisting of a single graphene cylinder. Different kinds of single-walled carbon nanotube are distinguished by the indices (n,m) which describe the vector along which the graphene is rolled. The chiral angle is the angle between the vector and the origin and can take any value between 0 and 30degree.
A molecule consisting of three or more concentric graphene cylinders.
A L-histidine derivative in which the methyl group is at N(tele)-position.
A N(alpha)-methyl-L-histidines  that is L-histidine bearing a single methyl substituent at the N(alpha)-position.
The second intermediate in the biosynthesis of vitamin B12 from uroporphyrinogen III, in which methyl groups have been introduced at positions 2 and 7 of the tetrapyrrole framework.
An N-formyl amino acid that is L-tyrosine in which one of the hydrogens of the amino group has been replaced by a formyl group.
A biphenyl compound comprising two tyrosine residues linked at carbon-3 of their benzene rings.
An optically active form of 2-hydroxybutyric acid having (R)-configuration.
An optically active form of 2-hydroxybutyric acid having (S)-configuration.
A succinic acid derivative having an imino group at the 2-position.
A gamma-glutamylalanine obtained by formal condensation of the gamma-carboxy group of L-glutamic acid with the amino group of L-alanine.
An aza-steroid that is a synthetic drug for the treatment of benign prostatic hyperplasia.
The D isomer of N-acetylglucosamine.
The (S)-enantiomer of 2-methylbutan-1-ol.
A hydroxy fatty aldehyde that is hexadecanal in which one of the hydrogens at position 2 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha-amylase (EC 3.2.1.1).
A cyclooxygenase inhibitor that interferes with the action of cyclooxygenase 2.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fipronil.
A cyclooxygenase inhibitor that interferes with the action of cyclooxygenase 1.
A nitroarene that is  naphthalene substituted by at least one nitro group.
